This paper deals with natural language processing and machine learning techniques for classification tasks, which are typically covered in the sub-categories of computational linguistics (cs.CL), machine learning (cs.LG), and artificial intelligence (cs.AI). Additionally, the paper involves the use of attention mechanisms, which are a popular area of research in neural networks and deep learning, and could be classified under the sub-category of cybernetics (cs.CY). Finally, the paper deals with information retrieval and classification of medical data, which could fall under the sub-category of information retrieval (cs.IR).
